comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. 100 µL T1. Abort after layer 1: printhead sticks in ink vat -> pressed on FEP film?

Global offset is -1.2. Rest #1 +100 µL T1. Printhead does not stick in ink vat. Pause after layer 10. Ink cured but formed disc with defects and slimy-soft. However, material can be compressed quite a lot before breaking -> higher tensile strength than pure GelMA.
next steps: Increase of exposure time from 5 to 7 s.

comment: Global offset is -1.2. 100 +100 (layer 11) +100 (layer 21) µL T1. Pause after layers 10 and 20. Finished print: minor parts stuck to FEP film. Print with medium defects. Channels completely closed. Sticky material. Suction forces during printing might produce defects as material seems very soft.
next steps: Rinsing of ink vat with DPBS. Decrease of Z hop speed from 150 to 50.

next steps: Decrease of exposure time from 7 to 5 s. Decrease of Z hop speed from 50 to 20.
